    <subsection>
        <title>List of Exponent Rules</title>

        <list xml:id="list-exponent-rules">
            <title>Exponent Rules</title>
            <introduction>
                <p>If <m>a</m> and <m>b</m> are real numbers, and <m>n</m> and <m>m</m> are positive integers, then we have the following rules:</p>
            </introduction>
            <dl>
                <li xml:id="exponent-rules-product">
                    <title>Product Rule</title>
                    <p><m>a^{n} \cdot a^{m} = a^{n+m}</m></p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="exponent-rules-power-to-power">
                    <title>Power-to-Power Rule</title>
                    <p><m>(a^{n})^{m} = a^{n\cdot m}</m></p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="exponent-rules-product-to-power">
                    <title>Product-to-Power Rule</title>
                    <p><m>(ab)^{n} = a^{n} \cdot b^{n}</m></p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="exponent-rules-quotient-of-powers">
                    <title>Quotient-of-Powers Rule</title>
                    <p><m>\dfrac{a^{n}}{a^{m}} = a^{n-m}</m></p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="exponent-rules-quotient-to-power">
                    <title>Quotient-to-Power Rule</title>
                    <p><m>\left( \dfrac{a}{b}  \right)^{n} = \dfrac{a^{n}}{b^{n}}</m></p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="exponent-rules-zero-exponent">
                    <title>Zero Exponent Rule</title>
                    <p><m>a^{0} = 1</m></p>
                </li>
            </dl>
        </list>
    </subsection>

